 Geometry in Action: Character recognition<body>

 
 
  
 
  
  Character recognition 
     Annotated
bibliography in on-line character recognition , J. R. Ward.
 
    Grouping words and multi-part symbols .
M. Burge and G. Monagan use Voronoi diagrams for document analysis.
 
    Medial axis
transformation and its application to seal imprint verification .
Y.-M. Fuh uses medial axis skeletonization as part of a method for detecting
forgeries in Chinese signature blocks.
 
    Tesarna Typesetter Program 
uses medial axes to produce carved lettering by a computer controlled router.
 
    US
Patent 5159645  performs character recognition by using convex hulls
to find the counters in each character. A similar idea also occurs in 
 Patent
4817166 .
 
    US
Patent 5483606  describes a method of registering (lining up) copied
pages with each other in a copying machine, using the convex hulls of
images of the pages.
 
     
Part of
 Geometry in Action ,
a collection of applications of computational geometry.  David Eppstein ,
 Theory Group ,
 ICS ,
 UC Irvine .  
